reviews.text: Very dog-friendly. Excellent food. One super organised and efficient lady taking orders, serving, playing with the dogs and managing the whole show. Will be visiting again for sure. The only gripe was that in a place teeming with dogs and kids, they really shouldn't be putting ceramic (BREAKABLE!) dogs right at the edge of each table. That's asking for trouble.
Very chilled place for having dinner with friend. Pet-friendly. Decent food. Serving Carlsberg. What’s the reason I won’t come again for some cheerful time with mates?😁

We ( two hoomans and two doggies) had lunch at Ocean in Pot today,  both the Truffle Mushroom Risotto and the Eggs Benedict were great! The Risotto was so creamy and rich, portion is good too! Probably enough for three people! The eggs-benedict was great too, the egg yorks really flooded! Together with the fresh salad as side dish, it perfected our lunch! I would definitely come back again and recommend this restaurant to the others :)
Nice view and very good customer service
